# NETRO Engineering Rules

NETRO is a mobile-first bilingual PWA intended for later Capacitor packaging.

## Architecture

- Keep UI components separate from business logic and data access.
- Never import mock data directly into route components.
- Access data through typed repository interfaces.
- Do not place supplier or payment API calls in frontend components.
- Do not expose supplier product IDs or supplier names to customers.
- Do not use `any`.
- Prefer discriminated unions for product and status models.
- Maintain strict TypeScript compatibility.

## Product Types

NETRO supports distinct product types:

- Gift cards
- Direct game top-ups

Do not model these as one undifferentiated product shape.

## Checkout

- Final prices must come from a quote.
- Payment confirmation is not fulfillment completion.
- Payment, fulfillment and refund statuses must remain separate.
- Direct top-ups should be limited to one per checkout in the initial release.

## Security

- Never store auth tokens, digital codes or sensitive order data in localStorage.
- Never include gift-card codes, Player IDs, emails, phone numbers or payment details in logs or analytics.
- Codes and identifiers must render LTR even in Arabic layouts.
- Sensitive code reveal must be treated as a server-controlled action in future backend integration.

## Localization

- Every user-facing string must be localized.
- Preserve full English LTR and Arabic RTL support.
- Do not hard-code text in route components.
- Official product and brand names should not be translated unless an official Arabic name exists.

## Platform

- Use the platform service abstraction instead of direct browser APIs.
- Features must respect platform capability flags.
- Do not introduce desktop-only layouts.
- Preserve safe areas and mobile touch targets.

## Change Discipline

- Work one implementation phase at a time.
- Do not redesign unrelated screens.
- Run typecheck and production build after every phase.
- Report all changed files and unresolved issues.